The VIP zone at Sunday’s Monaco Grand Prix was bursting with A-listers including supermodels Naomi Campbell and Heidi Klum. Naomi was not deterred by the rain that plagued the race and stepped out wearing a grey maxi dress with a pair of black and white trainers.She arrived on the arm of billionaire businessman, Ernesto Bertarelli, before mingling with fellow model Heidi.The America’s Got Talent star opted for a bold satin co-ord which featured a brightly coloured floral print.Heidi attended with her husband, Tom Kaulitz, and was seen chatting to Italian model Elisabetta Gregoraci who wore a bright green blazer dress.Other stars included Game Of Thrones' Kit Harington and Rose Leslie, Grey's Anatomy actor Patrick Dempsey, Bridgerton’s Simone Ashley and Euphoria villain Jacob Elordi.Princess Charlene of Monaco turned heads in a stunning blue jumpsuit as she accompanied her husband, Prince Albert, and their seven-year-old twins Gabriella and Jacques.Geri Horner was also there with her husband Christian and sported her usual all-white outfit.